  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the existing `RagIndexingPipeline` so a single pipeline instance can write
    chunked + embedded document content to EITHER the customer-corpus indexes
    (`spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` + `discovery-index` ŌĆö current behavior, unchanged) OR
    the new session-scoped `spaarke-session-files` index (R5 vertical slice ŌĆö new
    behavior). The target is selected per-call by the call site (D2-03
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` and D1-07 cleanup service in later tasks), NOT by a
    feature flag. Session-files writes MUST carry both `tenantId` AND `sessionId` on
    every indexed document per ADR-014.

    This is the canonical reuse-mandate task for R5: extend the existing pipeline,
    DO NOT build a parallel `SessionFilesIndexingPipeline`. The customer-corpus write
    path must remain behaviorally identical (back-compat for the existing wizard /
    knowledge-base / Insights-ingest call sites).

    R5 is configuration-first: no new feature flag, no new top-level `Program.cs` line.
    The pipeline is already registered conditionally in `AiModule.cs` (gated on
    `DocumentIntelligence:Enabled`); this task changes the SHAPE of the public API
    (adds a parameterized overload or target-mode parameter) WITHOUT changing the
    registration model.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer with deep familiarity with Azure AI Search SDK
    (`SearchClient`, `SearchIndexClient`, `MergeOrUpload`), Azure OpenAI embeddings,
    and Spaarke's RAG indexing internals. Comfortable extending an existing concrete
    sealed service with additive API surface while preserving every existing call
    site's behavior.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `RagIndexingPipeline` exposes a parameterized write path:

    - **Existing path** (`IndexDocumentAsync` ŌĆö unchanged signature): writes to
      knowledge + discovery indexes via the current logic (customer-corpus
      semantics). All existing call sites continue to compile and produce identical
      output (verified by `RagIndexingPipelineTests` continuing to pass without
      modification beyond additive new tests).

    - **New path** (`IndexSessionFileAsync` ŌĆö new method, OR `IndexDocumentAsync`
      overload with `IndexingTarget`): writes to the `spaarke-session-files` index
      ONLY (single chunk granularity per design ŌĆö session-files index uses the
      knowledge-chunk granularity, not the discovery-chunk granularity). The new
      method accepts `sessionId` (required), emits it on every indexed document
      alongside `tenantId`, and includes a parallel structured `IndexingCompleted` /
      `IndexingFailed` log line tagged with `sessionId`.

    Tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/RagIndexingPipelineTests.cs`
    exist for both paths: a new `IndexSessionFile_emits_tenantId_and_sessionId_on_every_doc`
    test asserts that the SearchClient receives a batch whose every document carries
    both fields; a new `IndexSessionFile_does_not_write_to_knowledge_or_discovery_indexes`
    test asserts the customer-corpus indexes are untouched on the new path; an
    existing-shape regression test asserts `IndexDocumentAsync` behavior is unchanged.

    DI registration in `AiModule.cs` is unchanged in shape ŌĆö the pipeline remains a
    conditionally registered concrete singleton; no new types are registered
    (`AnalysisServicesModule.cs` is NOT modified by this task per R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.3
    ŌĆö extension stays inside the existing module that already owns the pipeline).

    BFF publish-size delta measured per CLAUDE.md ┬¦10 + R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.6;
    expected Ōēł 0 MB (pure code reorganization + small API addition).
  </goal>

