  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Every document written to `spaarke-session-files` MUST carry BOTH `tenantId` AND `sessionId`. Both fields MUST be set on the indexed payload ŌĆö never null, never empty, never default. Failure to populate either is a defect.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism ŌĆö `RagIndexingPipeline` remains a concrete singleton registered conditionally inside `AiModule.cs` per existing pattern (AIPL-013). ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines. NO new interface introduced ŌĆö extend the concrete sealed class additively.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All R5 endpoints + services in BFF only. This task adds NO new endpoint and NO new service ŌĆö it extends an existing service's API surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. The session-files write path is selected by call-site parameter, NOT by a `SessionFiles:Enabled` flag. Kill-switch coverage inherits from existing `DocumentIntelligence:Enabled` gate around the pipeline registration.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene ŌĆö verify publish-size delta per task. Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline in task notes. Expected Ōēż +0.1 MB (pure code extension).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1 (Reuse Mandate)">MUST extend existing `RagIndexingPipeline` ŌĆö MUST NOT build a parallel `SessionFilesIndexingPipeline`, MUST NOT introduce a new `IIndexingPipeline` interface, MUST NOT duplicate the chunking/embedding loop. Cite this constraint in the implementation PR description.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.2">NO new feature flags. Target index is a CALL-SITE PARAMETER, not a configuration toggle.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.3">If a new DI registration becomes necessary (it should NOT for this task ŌĆö pipeline is already registered), it MUST be inside an existing feature module. ZERO new `Program.cs` lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.6">Per-task BFF publish-size verification mandatory. Report absolute + delta in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.7">Tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/RagIndexingPipelineTests.cs` MUST be added/updated for the new write path. Existing tests MUST continue to pass without modification (back-compat).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-02 / NFR-03">Multi-tenant + multi-session isolation ŌĆö `tenantId` + `sessionId` filters on every session-files index document; both fields drive query-time isolation in task 002.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-02">Files &lt; 500 tokens skip chunking (single-chunk index). Document this behavior in the new path; default behavior should produce one indexed document per file when content is small.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (back-compat)">Existing `IndexDocumentAsync(ParsedDocument, documentId, tenantId, fileName, speFileId, ct)` signature MUST remain unchanged. All current call sites in `KnowledgeBaseEndpoints.cs`, RagIndexingJobHandler (Service Bus path), Insights universal-ingest (`FilesIndexIngestDocumentSource`), and any other discovered call site must compile + behave identically without source modification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (idempotency)">The new session-files write path MUST be idempotent per ADR-004 pattern used by the existing path ŌĆö re-indexing the same `(documentId, sessionId)` MUST replace prior chunks, not duplicate them.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">Per BFF additions governance ŌĆö this task does NOT add a new endpoint or new package; it extends an existing service's surface area in place. No Placement Justification section required (in-place extension), but PR description MUST cite the reuse-mandate fulfillment.</constraint>
  </constraints>

