    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Existing pipeline shape (reference)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagIndexingPipeline.cs">
        The existing `IndexDocumentAsync` method: (1) chunks at two granularities
        (KnowledgeChunkingOptions = 2048ch/200 overlap; DiscoveryChunkingOptions =
        4096ch/400 overlap); (2) embeds via `_openAiClient.GenerateEmbeddingAsync`
        with a `SemaphoreSlim(MaxConcurrentEmbeddings = 16)`; (3) deletes stale
        chunks in parallel via `_ragService.DeleteBySourceDocumentAsync` (knowledge)
        + `DeleteDiscoveryChunksAsync` (discovery direct via `SearchClient`); (4)
        builds `KnowledgeDocument[]` via `BuildKnowledgeDocuments(...)`; (5) uploads
        via `_ragService.IndexDocumentsBatchAsync` (knowledge) +
        `UploadDiscoveryDocumentsAsync` (discovery direct). The new session-files
        path REUSES steps 1 (single granularity ŌĆö knowledge chunk settings), 2
        (embedding), and 4 (build docs with extra `SessionId` field). It uses a NEW
        helper `DeleteSessionFileChunksAsync` mirroring `DeleteDiscoveryChunksAsync`
        but filtering on `documentId + tenantId + sessionId`. It uses a NEW helper
        `UploadSessionFileDocumentsAsync` mirroring `UploadDiscoveryDocumentsAsync`
        but targeting `_aiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName` (NEW property on
        `AiSearchOptions` per this task ŌĆö see Step 4).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="KnowledgeDocument shape extension" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/KnowledgeDocument.cs">
        `KnowledgeDocument` currently carries `TenantId` but NOT `SessionId`. Add a
        nullable `SessionId` property (NOT serialized when null ŌĆö use
        `JsonIgnore(Condition = WhenWritingNull)` or equivalent) so existing
        knowledge-index + discovery-index writes are unchanged (back-compat) and
        session-files writes populate it. Confirm the matching `sessionId` field
        on the index JSON (task 001 owns the schema; field name MUST align). If
        the schema field is `Edm.String` filterable, the model property is
        `string?` with a `[SimpleField]` or `[SearchableField]` attribute matching
        the existing `TenantId` shape.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="AiSearchOptions extension" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/AiSearchOptions.cs">
        Add `SessionFilesIndexName` (`string`, init-only, default
        `"spaarke-session-files"`) following the same convention as
        `KnowledgeIndexName`, `DiscoveryIndexName`, `FilesIndexName`,
        `InsightsIndexName`. Admin-overridable via config in case the index name
        differs per environment (matches the precedent set by `FilesIndexName`).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="DI registration (no change required)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AiModule.cs">
        `RagIndexingPipeline` is registered conditionally inside the
        `if (documentIntelligenceEnabled)` block as a concrete singleton (AIPL-013;
        line 198 in current revision). This task does NOT touch the registration ŌĆö
        the new path is exposed via additive method on the existing concrete class.
        Per R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.3 zero new top-level lines + no new services to
        register.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Test conventions" location="tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/RagIndexingPipelineTests.cs">
        Existing tests use mocked `ITextChunkingService`, `IRagService`,
        `SearchIndexClient`, `IOpenAiClient`. Add new tests in the same file with
        the `IndexSessionFile_*` naming prefix; mock the `SearchClient` returned by
        `_searchIndexClient.GetSearchClient(SessionFilesIndexName)` to assert (a)
        every uploaded document carries `TenantId` AND `SessionId`; (b) the
        knowledge index client (`IRagService.IndexDocumentsBatchAsync`) is NEVER
        called on this path; (c) the discovery index client is NEVER called on
        this path; (d) idempotency ŌĆö re-indexing the same `(documentId, sessionId)`
        calls the session-files delete-then-upload sequence.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice. Users upload up
      to 20 files per chat session; those files must be chunked, embedded, and
      indexed into the new `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search index (provisioned
      by task 001) so the RAG search path (extended by task 002 with a `sessionId`
      filter) can scope grounded Q&amp;A retrieval and summarization to a single
      session. The indexing work is owned by THIS task.

      Design rationale (design.md ┬¦4.2, ┬¦4.4; spec.md Open Decisions): a dedicated
      session-files index ŌĆö rather than extending `spaarke-knowledge-index-v2` with
      a `sessionId` filter ŌĆö gives clean isolation, simple eviction (task 007's
      cleanup `IHostedService`), and avoids polluting customer-corpus query metrics
      with ephemeral session traffic. The pipeline that writes to it is the SAME
      pipeline that writes the customer corpus (per R5 reuse mandate) ŌĆö call sites
      choose the target.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="dependency">
        Task 001 provisions the `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search index on
        Spaarke Dev and authors `infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-session-files.json`
        with the exact schema (including the `sessionId` field shape) that THIS task
        must populate. This task can be authored against task 001's schema spec; the
        actual end-to-end write test requires task 001's index to exist on Spaarke
        Dev.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 002 (D1-02) extends `RagSearchOptions` with `SessionId` filter and
        routes `RagService.SearchAsync` to read FROM this new index. Together with
        task 003, the read-write pair lights up the session-files index.</item>
      <item>Task 007 (D1-07) is the cleanup `IHostedService` that DELETES from this
        index on session-end; it uses the same `SearchClient` /
        `SessionFilesIndexName` plumbing this task introduces. Task 007 depends on
        003.</item>
      <item>Task 012 (D2-03) `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` is the primary
        consumer of `IndexSessionFileAsync` ŌĆö invoked when a chat session uploads
        a file via the chat-pane file-chip flow.</item>
      <item>Existing knowledge-base reindex endpoint
        (`KnowledgeBaseEndpoints.cs` ŌåÆ `RagIndexingJobHandler` via Service Bus
        per ADR-001) is the canonical customer-corpus write call site. Its
        behavior MUST be unchanged by this task.</item>
      <item>Insights universal-ingest (`FilesIndexIngestDocumentSource`) reads from
        `spaarke-files-index`; not directly affected, but useful as a sibling
        per-index-name routing pattern.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

