    <step order="4" name="Plan Implementation ŌĆö API Shape Decision">
      Decide between (a) new method `IndexSessionFileAsync(ParsedDocument,
      documentId, tenantId, sessionId, fileName, speFileId, ct)` OR (b) overload
      of `IndexDocumentAsync` with an `IndexingTarget` enum parameter. RECOMMENDED:
      option (a) ŌĆö a dedicated new method. Rationale: (i) `sessionId` is REQUIRED
      for session-files writes (validated by `ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty`)
      but MUST NOT be present on customer-corpus writes; encoding it as a separate
      method removes a runtime branch + makes the call site intent explicit; (ii)
      back-compat is mechanically guaranteed ŌĆö the existing `IndexDocumentAsync`
      signature is literally untouched; (iii) cleaner test surface ŌĆö one test class
      per method shape; (iv) follows the existing pattern where the pipeline owns
      multiple public methods (knowledge + discovery internally; now add a session
      method). Record the decision in task notes with the rationale.
    </step>

    <step order="5" name="Implement ŌĆö AiSearchOptions Extension">
      Add `SessionFilesIndexName` property to
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/AiSearchOptions.cs`:

      ```csharp
      /// &lt;summary&gt;
      /// Name of the R5 session-scoped files index (provisioned by R5 task 001
      /// per spec.md ┬¦4.2 + ADR-014). Holds chunked + embedded content for files
      /// uploaded to a chat session. Documents carry both `tenantId` (per ADR-014)
      /// and `sessionId` (for session-scoped retrieval + eviction). Read by R5
      /// task 002 (RagService.SearchAsync session-scoped path); swept by R5 task
      /// 007 (SessionFilesCleanupJob). Default matches infra schema; admin-
      /// overridable per environment.
      /// &lt;/summary&gt;
      public string SessionFilesIndexName { get; init; } = "spaarke-session-files";
      ```

      Confirm no `appsettings.*.json` override is needed for Spaarke Dev (default
      matches task 001's provisioned index name).
    </step>

    <step order="6" name="Implement ŌĆö KnowledgeDocument SessionId Property">
      Add a nullable `SessionId` property to
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/KnowledgeDocument.cs` mirroring the
      `TenantId` attribute shape. Field MUST be:
      - `string?` (nullable ŌĆö null on knowledge + discovery index writes; set on
        session-files writes)
      - Serialized only when non-null (use the JSON serialization attribute
        convention already in use ŌĆö likely `[JsonPropertyName("sessionId")]` +
        `[JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]`)
      - Marked with the Azure Search SDK attribute that matches the schema field
        from task 001's `spaarke-session-files.json` (likely `[SimpleField(IsFilterable
        = true, IsFacetable = true)]` matching the `tenantId` attribute pattern)

      Verify by visual diff that `TenantId`'s attribute set is mirrored exactly
      with the appropriate JSON name. If `KnowledgeDocument` is shared across
      indexes whose schemas differ on `sessionId` presence, Azure Search SDK
      ignores absent fields on documents ŌĆö so a nullable property with
      WhenWritingNull is safe for the knowledge + discovery indexes that lack
      `sessionId`.
    </step>

    <step order="7" name="Implement ŌĆö `IndexSessionFileAsync` Method">
      Add the new public method to `RagIndexingPipeline.cs`:

      ```csharp
      public async Task&lt;PipelineIndexingResult&gt; IndexSessionFileAsync(
          ParsedDocument document,
          string documentId,
          string tenantId,
          string sessionId,
          string fileName,
          string speFileId,
          CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
      ```

      Implementation outline (mirrors `IndexDocumentAsync` but single-granularity
      + single-index):
      1. `ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(document)`;
         `ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(documentId)`;
         `ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(tenantId)`; `ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(sessionId)` (NEW ŌĆö
         ADR-014 contract);
         `ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(speFileId)`.
      2. Stopwatch + structured log "Starting session-files indexing for
         documentId={DocumentId} tenantId={TenantId} sessionId={SessionId}
         fileName={FileName}".
      3. Chunk text at knowledge granularity ONLY (single
         `KnowledgeChunkingOptions` call ŌĆö no discovery chunks). Per NFR-02:
         files &lt; 500 tokens skip chunking (single-chunk index) ŌĆö confirm the
         existing `ITextChunkingService` already produces a single chunk when
         input is small, or explicitly fall back to a single chunk if
         `document.Text` is below threshold.
      4. Generate embeddings via existing `GenerateEmbeddingsInBatchesAsync`.
      5. Get the session-files `SearchClient` via
         `_searchIndexClient.GetSearchClient(_aiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName)`.
      6. Delete stale chunks for `(documentId, tenantId, sessionId)` using a new
         private helper `DeleteSessionFileChunksAsync` modeled on
         `DeleteDiscoveryChunksAsync`; filter is
         `documentId eq '{escaped}' and tenantId eq '{escaped}' and sessionId eq '{escaped}'`.
      7. Build `KnowledgeDocument[]` via the existing `BuildKnowledgeDocuments`
         helper, but pass an additional `sessionId` parameter (extend the helper
         to accept optional `string? sessionId = null` ŌĆö default null preserves
         customer-corpus shape exactly). In the loop, set
         `docs[i].SessionId = sessionId`.
      8. Upload via a new private helper `UploadSessionFileDocumentsAsync` modeled
         on `UploadDiscoveryDocumentsAsync` (batched 1000;
         `MergeOrUploadDocumentsAsync`).
      9. Stopwatch.Stop + structured log
         `IndexingCompleted` variant (EventId 5202 ŌĆö new) including `SessionId` in
         the message template. Add the matching `LoggerMessage` partial method
         `LogSessionFileIndexingCompleted(string tenantId, string sessionId,
         string documentId, int chunksIndexed, long elapsedMs)`. Match the
         existing error-path log shape with EventId 5203
         `LogSessionFileIndexingFailed`.
      10. Return `PipelineIndexingResult { DocumentId, KnowledgeChunksIndexed =
          chunksIndexed, DiscoveryChunksIndexed = 0, DurationMs }`. (Keep the
          existing result shape; discovery count = 0 on this path. If a follow-on
          task wants a dedicated `SessionFilesChunksIndexed` field, add it
          additively then ŌĆö not in this task.)

      Add the helper extension to `BuildKnowledgeDocuments`:

      ```csharp
      private static IReadOnlyList&lt;KnowledgeDocument&gt; BuildKnowledgeDocuments(
          IReadOnlyList&lt;TextChunk&gt; chunks,
          IReadOnlyList&lt;ReadOnlyMemory&lt;float&gt;&gt; embeddings,
          string documentId,
          string tenantId,
