    <criterion testable="true">`RagIndexingPipeline.cs` exposes a new public method `IndexSessionFileAsync(ParsedDocument, documentId, tenantId, sessionId, fileName, speFileId, ct)` that compiles, is well-XML-documented, and follows the existing pipeline's logging + error-handling conventions.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The existing public method `IndexDocumentAsync(ParsedDocument, documentId, tenantId, fileName, speFileId, ct)` signature is BYTE-FOR-BYTE unchanged. All current call sites (KnowledgeBaseEndpoints + Service Bus + Insights ingest) compile without source modification.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every document written by `IndexSessionFileAsync` carries BOTH `TenantId` AND `SessionId` populated (non-null, non-empty), verified by unit test `IndexSessionFile_emits_tenantId_and_sessionId_on_every_doc`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`IndexSessionFileAsync` writes ONLY to `_aiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName` ŌĆö it does NOT call `IRagService.IndexDocumentsBatchAsync` (knowledge index) and does NOT call the discovery index `SearchClient`. Verified by unit test `IndexSessionFile_does_not_call_knowledge_or_discovery_indexes`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`IndexSessionFileAsync` throws `ArgumentException` when `sessionId` is null or empty. Verified by unit test `IndexSessionFile_throws_on_missing_sessionId`. Same for `tenantId` per ADR-014 contract.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`IndexSessionFileAsync` is idempotent ŌĆö the same `(documentId, tenantId, sessionId)` triple invoked twice results in the second invocation deleting prior chunks before re-uploading. Verified by unit test `IndexSessionFile_idempotency_deletes_before_upload`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`AiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName` defaults to `"spaarke-session-files"` matching task 001's provisioned index name; admin-overridable via config (precedent: `FilesIndexName`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`KnowledgeDocument.SessionId` is a nullable string (`string?`), null by default, serialized to JSON only when non-null, and tagged with the Azure Search SDK attribute mirroring `TenantId`'s shape. Existing knowledge + discovery index writes do NOT emit `sessionId` (back-compat).</criterion>
